    <Grid>
        <Label x:Name="Subtitle" Content="For loop" HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Top" FontFamily="Bebas Kai" FontSize="20" Margin="-1,-2,0,0" FontWeight="Bold"/>
        <TextBlock x:Name="Paragraph" HorizontalAlignment="Left" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" Margin="4,27,0,0" FontFamily="Bebas Kai" FontSize="16" Width="421"><Run Text="Next, the condition is evaluated. The condition is evaluated before the body of the loop is performed, so this is still considered a pre-test loop. If the condition is true, the body of the loop will execute. "/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="The &lt;post-loop-expr&gt; gets evaluated after the body of the loop is done executing. Normally, this section changes the control variable from &lt;init-expr&gt;.  Once the body has finished executing, the condition is checked again to determind if the loop is to continue. Let's view some examples of what you can do with a for loop."/></TextBlock>


